description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;***Internal Applicants Only***&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a General Adult Consultant Psychiatrist to join our crisis team at Langley Green Hospital, Crawley, West Sussex.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note this post attracts a Relocation Package of up to £8000. Information on this can be obtained from the Medical Staffing Team on 0300 304 0393.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Sussex Partnership we are committed to providing opportunities for &lt;strong&gt;flexible working&lt;/strong&gt;. If you would like to work differently or different hours to as advertised, please get in touch to discuss this in more detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Langley Green Hospital has some &lt;strong&gt;free on-site parking&lt;/strong&gt;. Also, if you haven’t thought about living in &lt;strong&gt;West Sussex&lt;/strong&gt; before then you should consider the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Journey from the coast to the countryside in minutes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoy a lifestyle where there are renowned cycle routes and picturesque walks, including the famous South Downs Way in the South Downs National Park!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embrace taking time to discover all the miles of scenic coastline, including West Wittering beach and Selsey.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Easy access to airports - Gatwick and Heathrow are both within 90 minutes of the county, providing links to Europe and beyond&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brighton and Hove or London are within easy reach via local and national bus routes and national mainline stations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team cares for adults of working age from Crawley, Horsham and the surrounding areas. You will be part of a friendly and supportive multidisciplinary team that consists of other Consultants, Nurse’s, Social Workers and more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust strives to maximise clinical time for doctors so you will benefit from an assigned 0.5 WTE of direct admin support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work with other acute services in the local area including the in-patient teams based at the hospital, and local assessment and treatment (ATS) community services There are separate services for older persons including those with a suspected or confirmed diagnosis of dementia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role can also support any interest in research, development, medical education or special interests that you may have. We strongly believe in creating roles that provide a service but also give you the opportunity to develop your own areas of special interest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is only so much we can say to you in an advert, so would love to speak to you about this role in more detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Claire TannerJob titleClinical Director West Sussex CDSEmail addressClaire.Tanner@sussexpartnership.nhs.ukTelephone number07710977985&lt;/p&gt;
